  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add onions and garlic; saut\u00e9 for about 3 minutes until softened.",
    "Stir in tomato paste, seasonings (Sazon blend, cumin, coriander), paprika, and vegetable stock cubes. Simmer for about 10 minutes to meld flavors.",
    "Add spinach leaves; cook until wilted. Reduce heat to low and continue simmering for an additional 5-7 minutes or until sauce thickens slightly.",
    "Serve hot over rice, couscous, or as a side dish with grilled vegetables."
